x'= Ax
A
\mathbb{R}^n
x'_i = \sum_j a_{ij} x_j
[A]_{ij} =a_{ij} = \frac{\partial x'_i}{\partial x_j}
\frac{\partial}{\partial x_i'} = \sum_j \frac{\partial x_j}{\partial x'_i} \frac{\partial}{\partial x_j}
\frac{\partial}{\partial x_i'} = \frac{\partial}{\partial \sum_j a_{ij} x_j} = \sum_j a_{ij} \frac{\partial}{\partial x_j} =  \sum_j \frac{\partial x'_i}{\partial x_j} \frac{\partial}{\partial x_j}
\frac{\partial}{\partial x_i'} = \frac{\partial}{\partial \sum_j a_{ij} x_j} = \sum_j a_{ij} \frac{\partial}{\partial x_j} 
